post_text:
The UP Elementary Administration would like to encourage our families to prepare for and respond to any impact from the storm. Below are some resources that may be useful:

United Way 2-1-1 is a public resource list that allows people to see what services are available by zip code.

The Governor‚Äôs Office of Homeland Security and Emergency Preparedness (GOHSEP) offers the Louisiana Emergency Preparedness Guide on their site and includes information on personal preparedness and state resources in the event of an event. GOHSEP also manages GetAGamePlan.org with additional resources, along with an app for Apple and Android devices.

Follow Red Stick Ready. Red Stick Ready is the Mayor‚Äôs Office of Homeland Security and Emergency Preparedness. Explore their website, like them on Facebook, follow them on Twitter, and sign up for alerts, so that you will always have the most up-to-date information about any threat, weather or event, affecting the parish.

post_text:
Hello UP Families!

As a response to recent events, Governor John Bel Edwards has closed all K-12 public schools in the state of Louisiana. Schools will be closed Monday, March 16, 2020 through Monday, April 13, 2020. Please understand this is an effort to slow the spread of COVID-19 in the state.
‚Ä¢
We have moved our instruction online, through Google Classroom. It is the same classroom that your students would normally sit in everyday, but now it is on the computer. Our students will see their teachers face everyday, be able to ask questions, continue to work with their classmates, complete assignments, and receive grades through Google Classroom. Teachers and Administrators are still here to assist you and your family with questions about the program as well as any other questions that apply.
‚Ä¢
Parents we will need your help to ensure that this is as smooth as possible. Please visit our website to access the parent guide to Google Classroom. Your students should be sitting next to you as you go through the presentation.

post_text: Watch Us Grow!

THEADVOCATE.COM
ExxonMobil donation supports YMCA swim lessons

Louisiana Association of Public Charter Schools
July 25, 2019 at 4:09 PM ¬∑

Congratulations UP Elementary Baton Rouge and ExxonMobil Baton Rouge!

University Preparatory Elementary School in Baton Rouge has seen a 25 percent increase in summer school attendance, which educators attribute in part to free swim lessons at the neighboring ExxonMobil YMCA.

Those free lessons are made possible by a $20,000 donation from ExxonMobil for lessons in swimming and water safety skills. More than 125 students from University Preparatory Elementary School are benefiting from the grant, according to a news release. Read more here: http://bit.ly/UPElementaryandExxonMobil.
